    <svcproc id="s26510.3.3" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Glow Plug Relay</title>
        <figure id="e3001138.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj09/J09044.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>IAH and glow plug relays</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">IAH relay</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow plug relay</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>It is mounted on the large support bracket behind the cab. The dust cover must be removed for access to
            the relay. The ECM controls the glow plug relay 2 that controls the glow plugs to warm the engine cylinders
            to aid cold engine starting and reduce exhaust emissions during warm-up. The glow plug relay is the shorter
            of the two relays.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
